verbose_text: Flagellin is detected by TLR-5 as well as NLRP3 (NLR family pyrin domain containing; previously NALP3) and NLRC4 (NLR family CARD domain containing; previously IPAF [IL-1beta-converting enzyme protease activating factor]), both of which activate caspase-1 in response to S. Typhimurium.
